title: Cat Gillespie: Opening New Doors to Collaborative Performance

media:group.media:title: Cat Gillespie: Opening New Doors to Collaborative Performance
media:group.media:description:
Cat's path through the School of Drama is expanding her understanding of her craft, creative risk-taking, and collaboration.

At the College of Performing Arts (CoPA), Cat has found opportunities to break the boundaries of dramatic performance, sparking growth as a playwright and collaborator. Her studies at CoPA's School of Drama have challenged her to take new risks, such as exploring playwriting, and revisit assumptions about collaboration and her craft. Looking back on her time as an undergraduate, Cat recalls she was "engaging creatively every minute" and doing things she thought she couldn't doâ€”on and off the stage.
